        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1963-05-29T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1963-05-29T00:00:00-05:00" n="104"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d104">
                <head>104. Message From President <persName corresp="#p_KJF2" type="from"
                        >Kennedy</persName> to Chairman <persName corresp="#p_KNS2" type="to"
                        >Khrushchev</persName>
                    <note n="0" type="source" xml:id="d104fn0">Source: Department of State,
                        Presidential Correspondence: Lot 77 D 163. No classification marking.
                        Another copy is in the Kennedy Library, National Security Files, Countries
                        Series, <gloss target="#t_USSR1">USSR</gloss>, <persName corresp="#p_KNS2"
                            >Khrushchev</persName> Correspondence.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>Washington</placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian"
                            when="1963-05-29">May 29, 1963</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Dear Mr. Chairman</hi>: I am happy to inform you that the
                    date of July 28, 1963, which you suggest for the arrival of Secretary <persName
                        corresp="#p_RD3">Rusk</persName> in Moscow, is satisfactory. I have asked
                    Secretary <persName corresp="#p_RD3">Rusk</persName> to get in touch with
                    Minister <persName corresp="#p_GAA1">Gromyko</persName> well in advance of this
                    date in order to work out the arrangements, including a public announcement at
                    an appropriate agreed time.<note n="1" xml:id="d104fn1">Printed from an unsigned
                        copy.</note>
                </p>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
